ommunes}}\n{{Urban Community of Bordeaux}}\n{{World Heritage Sites in France}}\n{{Higher Education in Bordeaux}}\n{{Prefectures of departments of France}}\n{{Prefectures of regions of France}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:Bordeaux| ]]<!--leave the empty space as standard-->\n[[Category:Communes of Gironde]]\n[[Category:Port cities and towns on the French Atlantic coast]]\n[[Category:Prefectures in France]]\n[[Category:World Heritage Sites in France]]\n[[Category:Cities in France]]\n[[Category:Gironde]]\n[[Category:Guyenne]]\n[[Category:Burdigalian| ]]\n", "name_user": "Jefunky", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eBuildings", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bordeaux"}
{"title_page": "Neha Dhupia", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2016}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2016}}\n{{Infobox pageant titleholder\n|name = Neha Dhupia\n|image = NehaDhupia (cropped).jpg\n|imagesize =\n|caption = Dhupia at the [[L'Or\u00e9al]] [[Femina (India)|Femina]] Women Awards, 2013\n|occupation = Actor\n|birth_place = [[Cochin]], [[Kerala]], India<ref name=\"auto\">{{cite web|title=Touchdown #kochi #kerela ... ( also my place of birth! )|url=https://twitter.com/NehaDhupia/status/408432283603853313|accessdate=12 April 2013}}</ref>\n|birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1980|08|27}}<ref>{{Cite web | title = Birthday Special: Neha Dhupia's FABULOUS life | work = Rediff | date = 27 August 2014 | accessdate = 2016-09-05 | url = http://www.rediff.com/movies/report/birthday-special-neha-dhupias-fabulous-life/20140827.htm }}</ref>\n|years_active = 2000\u2013present\n| spouse = {{marriage|[[Angad Bedi]]|2018-05-10}}\n| children =  1\n|height = \n|competitions = [[Femina Miss India|Femina Miss India 2002]]<br>(winner)<br>[[Miss Universe 2002]]<br>(Top-10 finalist)\n}}\n'''Neha Dhupia''' (born 27 August 1980) is an [[India|Indian]] actress who worked in [[Bollywood|Hindi]], [[Punjabi cinema|Punjabi]], [[Telugu cinema|Telugu]] and [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] films. Now she is one of the judges in [[MTV Roadies (season 16)]].She is also called as \"Fake Feminist\" or \"Bollywood ki Selena Gomez\".  She has won the 2002 [[Femina Miss India]] pageant.\n\n==Early life==\nDhupia was born in [[Kochi|Cochin]] (present-day Kochi), India to a [[Sikh]] family.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://bollywood.allindiansite.com/interviews/neha_dhupia.html|title=Neha Dhupia - It's all about the Bollywood|publisher=allindiansite.com|accessdate=2016-09-05|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20041210161701/http://bollywood.allindiansite.com/interviews/neha_dhupia.html|archive-date=10 December 2004|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=\"auto\"/> Her father, Commander Pradip Singh Dhupia, served in the [[Indian Navy]] and mother, Manpinder, (Babli Dhupia) is a homemaker. She went to [[Navy Children School Kochi|Naval Public School, Cochin]] then transferred to [[Navy Children School, Chanakyapuri]], New Delhi.{{citation needed|date=July 2019}} She graduated from [[Jesus and Mary College]] in New Delhi,  affiliated to the [[University of Delhi]], with honours in History.<ref>{{cite web|title=Shah Rukh Khan collects his degree after 28 years: 10 Bollywood stars who graduated from DU|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/education/story/10-bollywood-stars-who-passed-out-from-du/1/446162.html|website=India Today|accessdate=4 May 2016|date=17 February 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nDhupia made her acting debut in a play in New Delhi called ''[[Graffiti]]''. Thereafter she appeared in a music video for Indipop band [[Euphoria (Indian band)|Euphoria]] and modeled for advertisement campaigns. She then appeared in the TV serial ''Rajdhani''. In 2002, she participated in the Femina Miss India pageant, where she was crowned as Miss Universe India 2002. She was subsequently sent to the [[Miss Universe]] 2002 pageant in Puerto Rico where she placed in the top 10.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Daigle |first1=Katy |title=Five Miss Universe Finalists Picked |publisher=Associated Press |date=30 May 2002}}</ref> After placing in the pageant, Dhupia intended to pursue a career in the [[Indian Foreign Service]], but turned to acting instead.<ref>{{cite news |title=Air rare for Bollywood star |work=New Zealand Herald |date=14 October 2016}}</ref>\n[[File:Neha dhupia iifa press confrence 2012 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright=0.8|Dhupia at a press conference at the [[13th IIFA Awards]]]]\n\n===Film career===\nDhupia made her film debut in 1994 as a child artist in Malayalam film ''[[Minnaram]]'' starring [[Mohanlal]]. Her Bollywood debut was with the 2003 film ''Qayamat: City Under Threat'', which had an average performance at the box office. She rose to fame with her role ''[[Julie (2004 film)|Julie]]''<ref>{{cite news |title=Actress Neha Dhupia says handsome men aren't her type, but try cooking |publisher=The Canadian Press |date=24 August 2006}}</ref> and then appeared in ''[[Sheesha (2005 film)|Sheesha]]'' (2005) in a dual role of twin sisters but it did not do well at the box office. She then starred in films such as ''[[Kyaa Kool Hai Hum]]'' (2005) and ''[[Shootout at Lokhandwala]]'' (2007), which did well at the box office, and featured in a segment of the anthology film ''[[Dus Kahaniyaan]]'' (2007).\n\nIn the following years, Dhupia appeared in supporting roles in multiple films including ''[[Chup Chup Ke]]'' (2006), ''[[Ek Chalis Ki Last Local]]'' (2007), ''[[Mithya]]'' (2008), ''[[Maharathi (2008 film)|Maharathi]]'' (2008), ''[[Singh Is Kinng]]'' (2008)<ref>{{cite news |last1=Canning |first1=Simon |title=The lure of a vast Indian audience |work=The Australian |date=6 September 2007 |page=38}}</ref> and ''[[Dasvidaniya]]'' (2008). In 2011, she played [[Eva Braun]] in the film ''[[Dear Friend Hitler]]'' about Mahatma Gandhi.\n\n===Other===\nDhupia has modeled on the runway for designers such as [[Rohit Bal]] and D'damas.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Reddy |first1=Sujata |title=Such a ramp age |work=Hindustan Times |date=23 January 2009}}</ref>\nIn 2016, Dhupia conceptualized and hosted a [[Bollywood]] podcast called [[#NoFilterNeha]] on the Indian music app [[Saavn]], in which she interviews Bollywood celebrities. The show received positive reviews, with over 2.3 million listeners. Dhupia debuted season four in November 2019 and plans to expand the podcast into a web series.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Siingh |first1=Simran |title=Neha Dhupia on fourth season of her JioSaavn podcast: I'm glad most of my guests enjoy being 'unfiltered' |url=https://www.firstpost.com/entertainment/neha-dhupia-on-fourth-season-of-her-jiosaavn-podcast-im-glad-most-of-my-guests-enjoy-being-unfiltered-7602291.html |work=First Post |date=5 November 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life and off-screen work==\nDhupia has run in the [[Mumbai Marathon]] to support the Concern India Foundation and helped to raise over 5 lakhs.<ref>{{cite news|title=B-town celeb quotient high at Mumbai Marathon |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/articleshow/7296846.cms?prtpage=1|accessdate=7 October 2011 |newspaper=Times of India |date=16 January 2011|agency=IANS}}</ref> She also helped to raise money for victims of the [[2011 Sikkim earthquake]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Sen|first=Zinia|title=B'wood going all out to raise money|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/bollywood/news-interviews/Bwood-going-all-out-to-raise-money/articleshow/10204358.cms|accessdate=7 October 2011|newspaper=Times of India|date=2 October 2011}}</ref> She performed at the GR8 Women's Award 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiantelevisionacademy.com/site/awards_itawa_details.php?year=2012 |title = The ITA Awards \u00bb GR8! Women Achiever Awards|date=15 February 2012|work=IndianTelevisionAcademy.com |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130318111043/http://www.indiantelevisionacademy.com/site/awards_itawa_details.php?year=2012|archivedate=18 March 2013|accessdate=2016-09-05}}</ref>\n\nShe also participated in the Hiru Golden Film Awards 2014 in [[Sri Lanka]] as a special guest along with Bollywood actors such as [[Sunil Shetty]], [[Vivek Oberoi]], [[Anil Kapoor]], and actress [[Bipasha Basu]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hirugoldenfilmawards.lk/|title=Hiru Golden Film Awards |accessdate=2016-09-05 |publisher=hirugoldenfilmawards.hirutv.lk}}</ref>\n\nActor [[Angad Bedi]] began dating Neha while he was in a relationship with Nora Fatehi, Neha eventually got pregnant and the couple decided to get married 3 months into the pregnancy in a private ceremony at a Gurudwara on May 10, 2018. On November 18, 2018, she gave birth to their first child, a girl, Mehr Dhupia Bedi.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/neha-dhupia-angad-bedi-blessed-with-baby-girl/articleshow/66676967.cms|title=Neha Dhupia, Angad Bedi blessed with baby girl - Times of India|work=The Times of India|access-date=2018-11-18}}</ref> Neha Dhupia has been fat-shamed for her post-pregnancy weight gains by certain sections of the media.<ref>https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/life-style/parenting/moments/new-mom-neha-dhupia-gets-fat-shamed-for-her-post-pregnancy-weight/articleshow/67834620.cms</ref>\n\nIn March 2020 she was trolled on [[social media]] after a clip went viral on the internet of the reality show MTV Roadies where Dhupia threw abuses at a contestant(male) who slapped his girlfriend for allegedly cheating.   Some comments towards her described her reaction as hypocritical after she did not react similarly to a previous incident on Roadies where a female contestant on said she had slapped four men.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/neha-dhupia-accused-of-fake-feminism-after-rebuking-roadies-contestant-who-slapped-girlfriend-2194219|title=Neha Dhupia Accused Of 'Fake Feminism' After Rebuking Roadies Contestant Who Slapped Girlfriend|date=13 March 2020|accessdate=26 March 2020|author=Basu, Nilanjana}}</ref> where she said the famous line \"it's her choice. \" Neha stated that she stands by every single thing she said and decided to speak out after even her family members faced \"abuses and harassment\" on social media. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/entertainment/neha-dhupia-trolled-for-rebuking-roadies-contestant-who-slapped-girlfriend-stands-by-what-she-said-2194940|title=HNeha Dhupia, Trolled For Rebuking Roadies Contestant Who Slapped Girlfriend, Stands By What She Said: \"Abuse Not Acceptable\"}}</ref>\n\n==Filmography==\n{{unreferencedsection|date=September 2016}}\n\n===Films===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! Year !! Film !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n|-\n|1994\n|''[[Minnaram]]''\n|\n|Debut film- [[Malayalam]]- Child Artist\n|-\n| 2000 || ''Ninja Odoru! Ninja Densetsu'' || Meena || Japanese film\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2003|| ''[[Ninne Istapaddanu]]'' || || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film\n|-\n| ''[[Qayamat: City Under Threat]]'' || Sapna || Bollywood debut- Nominated- Filmfare Awards Best Debut Actress\n|-\n| ''Miss India: The Mystery'' || ||\n|-\n| ''[[Villain (2003 film)|Villain]]'' || Aisha || [[Telugu language|Telugu]] film<br />Remake of Tamil film ''[[Villain (2002 film)|Villain]]''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2004 || ''[[Julie (2004 film)|Julie]]'' || Julie ||\n|-\n| ''[[Rakht: What If You Can See the Future]]'' || Rhea Trehan || Special appearance\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2005 || ''Siskiyaan'' || Ayesha Sheikh ||\n|-\n| ''[[Sheesha (2005 film)|Sheesha]]'' || Sia/Ria Malhotra ||  Double role\n|-\n| ''[[Kyaa Kool Hai Hum]]'' || Dr. Rekha ||\n|-\n| ''[[Garam Masala (2005 film)|Garam Masala]]'' || Maggi ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2006 || ''[[Fight Club \u2013 Members Only]]'' || Komal || Special appearance\n|-\n| ''[[Teesri Aankh: The Hidden Camera]]'' || Sapna ||\n|-\n| ''[[Chup Chup Ke]]'' || Meenakshi || Credited as Bandya\n|-\n| ''[[Utthaan]]'' || Kiran Talreja ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"5\"|2007 || ''[[Delhii Heights]]'' || Suhana ||\n|-\n| ''[[Ek Chalis Ki Last Local]]'' || Madhu ||\n|-\n| ''[[Shootout at Lokhandwala]]'' || Rohini ||\n|-\n| ''[[Heyy Babyy]]'' || Special appearance in song ||\n|-\n| ''[[Dus Kahaniyaan]]'' || || ([[Anthology film]]) story ''[[Dus Kahaniyaan#Plot|Strangers in the Night]]''\n|-\n|rowspan=\"7\"|2008 || ''[[Rama Rama Kya Hai Drama]]'' || Shanti ||\n|-\n| ''[[Mithya]]'' || Sonam ||\n|-\n| ''[[Kabhi Pyar Na Karna]]'' || || Pakistani film in [[Urdu]]\n|-\n| ''[[De Taali]]'' || Sara || Special appearance\n|-\n| ''[[Singh Is Kinng]]'' || Julie ||\n|-\n| ''[[Dasvidaniya]]'' || Neha Dhanot ||\n|-\n| ''[[Maharathi (2008 film)|Maharathi]]'' || Mallika ||\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\"|2009 || ''[[Paying Guests]]'' || Aarti Gupta ||\n|-\n| ''[[Bollywood Hero]]'' || Lalima Lakhani || Indian-American [[miniseries]]\n|-\n| ''[[De Dana Da